This repository includes small Mono example applications in C# that use rs-485 port of the raspicomm.

- rs485_write
 An example application that sends a Hello World message over the rs-485 port.

- rs485_read
 An example application that receives 10 bytes from the rs-485 port and displays them afterwards.

Required Prerequisites:
  - Mono
    'sudo apt-get install mono-mcs'

  - raspicomm rs485 device driver
    you can use the the script from https://gist.github.com/8/5029497 to install the kernel module

How to use the examples:
0. use git to clone this repository 
 'git clone https://github.com/amescon/rpc-mono-examples.git'

1. build the examples applications with make and run them
 1.1 rs485_write
  'cd Rs485Write'
  'make'
  './rs485_write.exe'

 1.2 rs485_read
  'cd Rs485Read'
  'make'
  './rs485_read.exe'

2. modify the code and play around with it